Yom Kippur is a sacred day for Jewish communities worldwide, where they fast, reflect, and seek forgiveness. The article expresses solidarity with those affected by Hurricane Ian, especially those unable to observe Yom Kippur in their synagogues. It emphasizes the importance of growth and improvement for individuals and communities. The author encourages everyone to address injustice and inhumanity in the world and commit to repairing what is broken. Finally, they extend well wishes for an easy and meaningful fast and hope for being sealed in the Book of Life.